  <div class="body">

  <!-- ================= EXEC SUMMARY ================= -->
  <section>
    <h2><span class="n">1.</span>Executive Summary</h2>
    <p class="lead">Vinyas is a Mysuru-based Electronics Manufacturing Services (EMS) company that has quietly become one of India's more specialised <strong>defence &amp; aerospace</strong> contract manufacturers. It runs a high-mix, low-to-medium-volume, build-to-print / build-to-spec model for complex PCB assemblies and box-builds, with the right gatekeeper credentials (AS9100-D, defence industrial licence, NADCAP, ISO 13485). Roughly <strong>85–90% of its order book is defence/aerospace</strong> and ~50% of revenue is exported to Europe and the US.</p>
    <p>The numbers have inflected hard. Revenue compounded at ~20% over FY21–FY26 to <strong>₹514 cr</strong>, but profitability is the real story: EBITDA margin expanded from ~6% to <strong>12.6%</strong> and PAT went from ₹1.2 cr (FY21) to <strong>₹30.9 cr (FY26)</strong>. A ₹1,309 cr order book (~2.5× FY26 revenue) and only 35–40% capacity utilisation give multi-year, operating-leverage-rich visibility, and management guides to 30–35% revenue growth into FY27.</p>
    <p>The catch — and it is a serious one — is <strong>cash conversion</strong>. The cash conversion cycle has stretched to ~232 days, receivable days have doubled to ~161, and despite ₹31 cr of reported FY26 profit, <strong>operating cash flow was roughly –₹32 cr and free cash flow about –₹77 cr</strong>. Growth is being funded by working-capital debt and equity dilution (a ₹150 cr warrant raise in 2025). At ~57× trailing earnings, ~8× book and ~32× EV/EBITDA, the stock already prices in flawless execution.</p>
    <div class="box note">
      <div class="bt">Bottom line</div>
      A high-quality, structurally well-positioned franchise riding India's defence-indigenisation and EMS tailwinds — but expensive and cash-flow-risky today. We would own the story on pullbacks and on evidence that cash collection is normalising, rather than chase it at a near-record multiple.
    </div>
  </section>

