    <div class="box note" style="margin-top:18px;">
      <div class="bt">Verdict — Hold / Accumulate on dips</div>
      Vinyas is a real franchise in the right place at the right time, and the order book plus operating-leverage runway make the growth case credible. But two things hold us back from an outright Buy at ₹1,405: a valuation that already discounts two years of flawless execution, and a working-capital profile that is turning reported profit into <em>negative</em> cash. We would build a position on meaningful pullbacks and, above all, on evidence that receivable days are falling and operating cash flow is turning durably positive. Until then, the risk/reward is balanced rather than compelling. <strong>Position sizing should respect its small-cap/SME liquidity.</strong>
